{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1772558273,"nonce":"b4li9sYUUt0jusE1LEEgXmhwUCI=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOQ241x87vbSohzqdi05o"},"target":"b6ee121025b7e8bcf15a5a905e1bc05118ccabe1cd377503617a0634468d47fd","message":"## Context\n\nFollow-up to #325 (ADR-0007: Retain Make with dependency tracking). Implements the\nADR's recommendation and the target taxonomy agreed in #335.\n\nPart of #263 (Simplify scripts and Makefile interface).\n\n## Problem\n\nThe current Makefile has 19+ targets that are all independent — no dependency graph.\nA fresh-clone workflow requires the user to know and run `make bootstrap`,\n`make setup-all`, and `make build` in the correct order. Re-running setup when nothing\nchanged wastes time. Several info/status scripts overlap.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis issue bundles the stamp-file Makefile rewrite with the related script\nconsolidation — doing them together avoids rewriting the Makefile twice.\n\n### Makefile Rewrite\n\nPer the agreed design in #335:\n\n**Tier 1 — Setup chain (stamp-based):**\n```\nbootstrap → setup-dev → manifest → per-layer setup → build\n```\n- Stamp files in `.make/` (gitignored) track completion\n- Per-layer stamps re-trigger when `.repos` files change\n- `setup-all` stays as a convenience target\n- Per-layer targets (`setup-core`, `setup-underlay`, etc.) removed\n- `format` removed — `lint` covers it\n\n**Tier 2 — Developer workflow:**\n| Target | Purpose | Dependencies |\n|---|---|---|\n| `build` | Build everything (auto-setup if needed) | Tier 1 chain |\n| `test` | Test everything | `build` |\n| `lint` | All pre-commit hooks | `setup-dev` stamp |\n| `clean` | Remove build artifacts + stamps | None |\n| `dashboard` | Unified coordination view | None (read-only) |\n| `validate` | Pass/fail workspace check (CI) | None (read-only) |\n| `help` | Self-documenting target list | None |\n\n**Tier 3 — Agent/maintenance:** unchanged (see #335).\n\n### Script Consolidation\n\n- **Merge `status_report.sh` + `health_check.sh`** into a `dashboard.sh` script\n  backing the new `dashboard` target\n- **Remove format-specific scripting** if any exists outside pre-commit\n- **Audit remaining scripts** — identify any that are unused or redundant after\n  recent worktree and identity work\n- **`sync` integration** — decide whether `dashboard` calls sync or sync remains\n  independent (currently `status_report.sh` syncs by default, `--quick` skips it)\n\n### Targets Removed or Merged\n\n| Current Target | Fate |\n|---|---|\n| `setup-core`, `setup-underlay`, `setup-platforms`, `setup-sensors`, `setup-simulation`, `setup-ui` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `format` | Removed — `lint` covers it |\n| `status` | Merged into `dashboard` |\n| `status-quick` | Merged into `dashboard QUICK=1` |\n| `health-check` | Merged into `dashboard` |\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. **`make build` from fresh clone** — automatically runs bootstrap → setup-dev →\n   manifest → layer setups → build (with first-run prompt unless `CI=1` — prompt\n   details in #330)\n2. **Incremental re-runs** — skip already-completed steps; re-run layer setup only\n   when its `.repos` file changes\n3. **`make test` depends on `make build`** — setup handled transitively\n4. **`make lint` depends on `setup-dev` stamp** — venv created automatically\n5. **`make dashboard`** — unified view replacing status/health-check\n6. **`make clean`** — removes build artifacts AND `.make/` stamps (full reset)\n7. **Preserve `make help`** — self-documenting targets\n8. **Preserve `generate-skills`** — slash command generation unaffected\n9. **`.make/` gitignored** and shared across worktrees (setup is workspace-global)\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Stamp invalidation strategy: simple touch vs hash-based (detect when scripts change)?\n- Should `dashboard` call `sync` by default or require explicit `make sync` first?\n- Manifest symlink guard — verify symlink exists before trusting its stamp?\n- Which of the 42 scripts in `.agent/scripts/` are unused and can be removed?\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Depends on #325 (ADR accepted)\n- Must not break `generate-skills` / slash command pattern\n- First-run interactive prompt is #330's scope — this issue just needs to leave\n  a clean hook point for it in the stamp chain\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #263 — Simplify scripts and Makefile interface (parent)\n- #325 — ADR-0007: Retain Make with dependency tracking (decision)\n- #335 — Target taxonomy and dashboard concept (design)\n- #330 — First-run initialization UX (follow-up)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1772547229,"nonce":"0NcNqCmKh0j6fTJTqxpZ+ojNV1I=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87vbSohzwAAAAVohOdf"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":2,"timestamp":1772558273,"nonce":"OdP/o8uQesKlg2kJ+aNT37QidEE=","metadata":{"github-id":"RTE_lADOQ241x87vbSohzwAAAAVo20Kl"},"title":"Refactor Makefile with stamp-file dependencies and consolidate scripts","was":"Refactor Makefile with stamp-file dependencies and consolidate scripts"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772558772,"nonce":"o9LOXTt7XV6AGIj5q/rM5dn/H8I=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87t-M1C","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/332#issuecomment-3992505666"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Watch — this is a large change (Makefile rewrite + script consolidation + new dashboard script) but the bundling is justified: doing them separately would mean rewriting the Makefile twice. The risk is PR size — this will touch the Makefile, `.gitignore`, potentially merge/rename/remove scripts, and update documentation. Consider splitting into 2-3 atomic commits within a single PR: (1) stamp-file Makefile + target cleanup, (2) dashboard script consolidation, (3) doc updates.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — Makefile and `.agent/scripts/` are workspace infrastructure.\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- Depends on #325 (ADR-0007) — in review, no code dependency\n- #335 (target taxonomy) — design agreed, captured in issue body\n- Blocks #330 (first-run UX) — needs the stamp chain hook point\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Enforcement over documentation | **OK** | Stamp-file dependencies enforce setup ordering mechanically instead of documenting it in a README |\n| Only what's needed | **OK** | Removes 6 per-layer targets, merges 3 status targets, removes `format` — net reduction in surface area |\n| Improve incrementally | **Watch** | Large scope for one issue. Mitigate with atomic commits within the PR. If the dashboard merge proves complex, it could be deferred to a follow-up without blocking the stamp-file work. |\n| A change includes its consequences | **Action needed** | See Consequences section — several downstream updates required |\n| Human control and transparency | **Watch** | `make build` auto-running `bootstrap` (which calls `sudo apt install`) on a fresh clone is a surprise. The first-run prompt (#330) addresses this, but until #330 lands there's a gap. Consider a guard: if bootstrap stamp doesn't exist, print \"First run detected — run `make setup-all` first\" rather than silently bootstrapping. |\n| Capture decisions, not just implementations | **OK** | Decision recorded in ADR-0007, design in #335 |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | **OK** | All changes are workspace infra |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0007 — Retain Make with dependency tracking | **Yes** | This is the implementation of the ADR |\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | **Yes (trivially)** | Makefile remains generic — no project-specific targets |\n| 0002 — Worktree isolation | **Yes** | Work must be done in a worktree. `.make/` being workspace-global and shared across worktrees is noted in the issue — verify this doesn't cause conflicts when multiple worktrees build concurrently |\n\n### Consequences\n\nPer the consequences map, this issue changes scripts and the Makefile:\n\n| If we change... | Also update... | Noted in issue? |\n|---|---|---|\n| Scripts in `.agent/scripts/` | Script reference table in `AGENTS.md` | **No** — `AGENTS.md` lists scripts; removed/renamed/merged scripts need table updates |\n| Scripts in `.agent/scripts/` | `Makefile` if it has a target | Yes — that's the core of this issue |\n| Framework skills (`.claude/skills/`) | Regenerate skills | **Partially** — removing `make status`, `make format`, `make health-check` targets will orphan their `/make_*` slash commands. Must run `make generate-skills` and add new `make dashboard` skill. |\n| `.gitignore` | — | Need to add `.make/` |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Update `AGENTS.md` script reference table** as part of this PR — scripts that are removed, renamed, or merged need to be reflected there.\n2. **Regenerate slash commands** — removing targets orphans `/make_status`, `/make_format`, `/make_health_check`, `/make_status_quick` skills. Add `/make_dashboard`. Run `make generate-skills` as a final step.\n3. **Bootstrap guard before #330 lands** — rather than having `make build` silently run `sudo apt install` on a fresh clone, consider a pre-bootstrap check that tells the user what's about to happen. This bridges the gap until #330 adds the proper first-run prompt.\n4. **Atomic commits** — suggest splitting into: (a) stamp-file Makefile + removed targets + `.gitignore`, (b) dashboard script consolidation, (c) `AGENTS.md` + slash command regeneration. Keeps the PR reviewable.\n5. **Resolve open questions during planning** — the 4 open questions (stamp invalidation, dashboard sync, manifest guard, unused scripts) should be answered in the `/plan-task` step, not left for implementation.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772645211,"nonce":"6VGQl/2biORfXcs8uGYywQu7cRE=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87vbSohzwAAAAVq4sXK"},"status":2}]}